(2778, 149, '_elementor_data', '[{"id":"jvlsiop","elType":"section","settings":[],"elements":[{"id":"jsxeknj","elType":"column","settings":{"_inline_size":"","_column_size":100},"elements":[{"id":"daflfhe","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<h2 style=\\"text-align: left;\\"><strong>FACE ANALYSIS AND SYNTHESIS<\\/strong><\\/h2><p>\\u00a0<\\/p><h3><strong>PEOPLE<\\/strong><\\/h3><p><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/perso\\/chabert_car\\/\\">Caroline Chabert<\\/a> ( Ph.D. Student 20012-2015 )<br \\/> Face retargetting<\\/p><p><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/perso\\/manceau_jer\\/\\">J\\u00e9r\\u00f4me Manceau<\\/a> ( Ph.D. Student 20012-2015 )<br \\/> Face cloning<\\/p><p><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/perso\\/salam_han\\/\\">Hanan Salam<\\/a> ( Ph.D. Student 20010-2013 )<br \\/> 3D objects face model<\\/p><p><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/perso\\/rseguier\\/\\">Renaud S\\u00e9guier<\\/a> (PhD, HDR )<\\/p><p><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/perso\\/soladie_cat\\/\\">Catherine Soladie<\\/a> ( Ph.D. Student 20010-2013 )<br \\/> Online expression analysis<\\/p><h3>RESEARCH TOPICS<\\/h3><p>We detect, analyse and synthesize faces for Video-Telephony, Man-Machine Interaction and Software Radio. Forces are concentrated on 2D and 2.5D Active Appearence Models (AAM) for wich we develop different pre-processing and new optimisation algorithms. Those AAM are implemented in real-time for embedded systems.<\\/p><h2><strong>RESEARCH PROJECTS<\\/strong><\\/h2><h3><strong>REPLICA, 2012 - 2015<\\/strong><\\/h3><p>Rehabilitation of facial praxis among cerebral paralysis via interactive Avatar.<br \\/> National collaborative project \\"ANR - TECHSAN\\"<br \\/> Leader: University of Rennes II (M2S, CRP2C).<br \\/> Partners: Saint Maurice Hospital, Dynamixyz, Sup\\u00e9lec.<br \\/> Contributions:<br \\/> Specification, metrics analysis: University of Rennes II<br \\/> Tests and validations: Saint Maurice Hospital<br \\/> Facial animation: Dynamixyz<br \\/> Face analysis: Sup\\u00e9lec<\\/p><h3><b>SKETCHER, 2012 - 2013<\\/b><\\/h3><p>Development of a Rapid E-Learning tool.<br \\/> Regional \\"PME\\" project funded by R\\u00e9gion Bretagne.<br \\/> Leader: Dynamixyz.<br \\/> Partners: Voxygen, Sup\\u00e9lec.<br \\/> Contributions:<br \\/> Specification, Integration: Dynamixyz<br \\/> Expressiv voice synthesis: Voxygen<br \\/> Face and gesture analysis: Sup\\u00e9lec<\\/p><p><b>IMMERSIVITE, 2011 - 2012<\\/b><\\/p><p>IMmersion dans un environnement de forMation convERsationnel, expresSIf et VIrTuEl<br \\/> Web site : <a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.immersivite.fr\\/\\">www.immersivite.fr <\\/a><br \\/> Integration of man-machine interfaces for serious-game. The objective is to increase the interaction efficienty between students and virtual characters.<br \\/> Regional \\"PME\\" project funded by R\\u00e9gion Bretagne.<br \\/> Leader: Dialonics.<br \\/> Partners: CERV, Dynamixyz, Sup\\u00e9lec, Virtualis.<br \\/> Contributions:<br \\/> 3D virtual world: CERV<br \\/> Facial animation: Dynamixyz<br \\/> Face and gesture analysis: Sup\\u00e9lec<br \\/> Natural language inetraction: Dialonics<br \\/> Product integration: Virtualis<\\/p><h3><b>IMMEMO, 2010 - 2013<\\/b><\\/h3><p>IMMersion 3D bas\\u00e9e sur l''interaction EMOtionnelle<br \\/> Web site : <a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/immemo\\/\\">www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/immemo\\/ <\\/a><br \\/> This industrial research project aims at designing a plug-in making it possible to capture and recognize the expressions of the face of a person immersed in a 3D virtual world for serious-game. The plugin will facilitate her interaction with an autonomous conversational agent (ACA) of which the behavior will adapt in a semi-automatic way to that of learning immersive person.<br \\/> National collaborative project \\"ANR - CONTINT\\"<br \\/> Leader: Sup\\u00e9lec<br \\/> Partners: Artefacto, Institut Telecom, ISIR.<br \\/> Contributions:<br \\/> 3D virtual world: Artefacto<br \\/> Facial expressions analysis: ISIR, Sup\\u00e9lec<br \\/> Multi-modal interaction: Institut Telecom<\\/p><h2><strong>PUBLICATIONS<\\/strong><\\/h2><p><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/perso\\/rseguier\\/publications.php\\">Patents, Journals, Conferences<\\/a><\\/p><p><b>DEMO<\\/b><\\/p><p><img class=\\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-150\\" src=\\"http:\\/\\/localhost\\/wordpress\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/05\\/HigherLayer.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"320\\" height=\\"240\\" \\/><\\/p><p>[embed]http:\\/\\/www.dailymotion.com\\/video\\/x2e30d_avatar_tech[\\/embed]<\\/p><p>Avatar<\\/p><h2><b>PAST RESEARCH PROJECTS<\\/b><\\/h2><h3><b>Lipsync<\\/b><\\/h3><p>Regional project \\"fonds de maturation\\" funded by R\\u00e9gion Bretagne and Feder.<br \\/> Synchronization of 3D character lips movment and shapes on an audio input.<br \\/> Ended in 2010.<\\/p><h2><b>PAST RESEARCHERS<\\/b><\\/h2><p><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/perso\\/nstoiber\\/\\">Nicolas Stoiber<\\/a> ( Ph.D. Student 2007-2010 )<br \\/> Facial Expressiveness of Virtual Characters<\\/p><p>Biyi Lin ( Ph.D. Student 2008-2009 )<br \\/> Emotion Classification<\\/p><p>Abdul Sattar ( Ph.D. Student 2006-2009, Post Doc 2010 )<br \\/> 3D face Active Appearence Models<br \\/> Lip Synchronization<\\/p><p>Yasser Aidarous ( Ph.D. Student 2005-2008 )<br \\/> Active Appearence Models optimisation for face analysis<\\/p><p><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/sylvain.legallou.fr\\/\\">Sylvain Le Gallou<\\/a> ( Ph.D. Student 2004-2007 )<br \\/> Active Appearence Models for face gesture analysis<\\/p><p>Olivier Dumas ( Ph.D. Student 2003-2006 )<br \\/> 3D face modelisation<\\/p><p>Nicolas Cladel ( Ph.D. student 2002-2005 )<br \\/> Multi-objectives snakes optimisation : application on mouth segmentation<\\/p><p>David Mercier ( Ph.D. student 2000-2003)<br \\/> Lipsreading<\\/p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":