(2783, 144, '_elementor_data', '[{"id":"apmindd","elType":"section","settings":[],"elements":[{"id":"deepyry","elType":"column","settings":{"_inline_size":"","_column_size":100},"elements":[{"id":"dbwyfyy","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<h2><strong>Optimisation de ressources fr\\u00e9quentielles<\\/strong><\\/h2><p>Following our previous model (see table 2), sensors of the lower layer comprise, among others, the physical layer sensors and particularly the hole detection sensor.<br \\/> One of the main objectives of Cognitive Radio is to reach an efficient spectrum management by using free bands in the spectrum. This implies to observe if the received signal, at any time, comprises only noise or also a telecommunication signal.<\\/p><h2><strong>Hole detection sensor<\\/strong><\\/h2><p>This sensor is extensively studied in the literature under the name, sensing. The CR is often limited to this sensor for detecting holes (or white spaces) in the spectrum as already discussed in Chapter 1. Cognitive radios require that the secondary network users are able to detect free spaces in the spectrum and use them in such a way that they do not interfere with the transmissions of the primary network. The quality of service required by the primary network will be otherwise significantly decreased. The problem of detection of primary network activity can be cast as a simple energy detection problem, for which various work efforts and methods exist since 1960. See Chapter 3 of book [Pal].<\\/p><p>In this area two thesis have been defended in 2008 and in 2013:<\\/p><ul><li><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/rd\\/scee\\/theses\\/ghozzi_2008.html\\">Des terminaux multi modes aux terminaux intelligents sensibles \\u00e0 leur environnement<\\/a>. Architecture d''un terminal Radio Cognitive (M. GHOZZI)<\\/li><li><a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.rennes.supelec.fr\\/ren\\/rd\\/scee\\/theses\\/khalaf_2013.html\\">Contributions \\u00e0 l\\u2019\\u00e9tude de d\\u00e9tection des bandes libres dans le contexte de la radio intelligente<\\/a> (Z. KHALAF)[Pal] Palicot J (Edited by), Radio Enineering: From Software radio to Cognitive Radio, Wiley, August 2011; ISBN: 978-1-84821-296-1<\\/li><\\/ul>","_animation":"fadeInUp"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":false}],"isInner":false}]'),
